sun.jvm.hotspot.utilities.soql

Interface ScriptObject

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultScriptObject, JSJavaArray, JSJavaClass, JSJavaField, JSJavaFrame, JSJavaHeap, JSJavaInstance, JSJavaMethod, JSJavaObjArray, JSJavaObject, JSJavaScriptEngine, JSJavaString, JSJavaThread, JSJavaTypeArray, JSJavaVM, JSList, JSMap, JSMetadata, MapScriptObject, SOQLEngine

    public interface ScriptObject
    Any Java object supporting this interface can be accessed from scripts with "simpler" access pattern. For example, a script engine may support natural property/field access syntax for the properties exposed via this interface. We use this interface so that we can dynamically add/delete/modify fields exposed to scripts. If we stick to JavaBean pattern, then property set is fixed.
